────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
IF SOMETHING GOES WRONG
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

Dashboard shows "connection error" or red status:
  → Run:  docker-compose ps
  → Any container not "Up"?  Run:  docker-compose up -d
  → Wait 15 seconds and refresh the browser

Phase 2 burst shows no anomaly events:
  → The baseline may not have warmed up yet (needs ~15s of traffic).
  → Wait for the Allow counter on the Live Demo page to climb to 150+,
    then click Burst Anomaly.
  → If the demo IP was recently blocked (from escalation), click Reset
    first — the anomaly baseline rebuilds automatically after reset.

All counters already show high numbers from a previous run:
  → Click Reset to clear demo state. Counters reset to 0.
  → Baseline rebuilds in ~15s — then all demos are ready again.

Need to fully wipe everything (including MongoDB):
  → docker-compose down -v && docker-compose up -d
  → This wipes all SQLite databases and MongoDB data.
  → Wait ~30s for all services to pass health checks.
